On Wednesday evening we completed a three day visit to Sweden and returned to my country. This was the first visit to Turkey from Sweden to the President.
The weather in Stockholm was pretty cold. The sea in front of our hotel caught ice. http://t.co/1omhgyszzg
The official welcome ceremony was very spectacular. We entered the Saraya with cars. http://t.co/t9mtkckd3g
Despite the cold weather, Turkish citizens living in Sweden are in the hands of palace gardens ...
... Turkish and Swedish flags greeted us. http://t.co/ıyqal8qksy
We also greeted the audience of the ceremony. http://t.co/qwayuv2chd
The "Serafim" was awarded to the President of the state and government by the Swedish Royal.
The King and I also put on our mutual engagement. http://t.co/eglb0h9vpv
All the scouting was done at the Royal Palace dinner.
Representatives of some Turkish society living in Sweden were also invited. http://t.co/ekafsduomj
The foreign ministers of the two countries have signed the "Strategic Partnership Agreement" with the Swedish Prime Minister and me. http://t.co/4kuagqusvt
We have held meetings with CEOs of Sweden's major companies around the world. http://t.co/s8vduiauyq
Outside view of the Stockholm City Hall. http://t.co/aswzv087bv
"Blue Hall" located at the entrance of the Municipal Palace is the place where the Nobel food of 1300 people is given. http://t.co/anzgxywokl
In the "Golden Hall" located on the upper floor, after the Nobel dinner, a music show was made.
The City Council President Margareta Björk gave a meal to you. http://t.co/gefds5h6cp
The mosaic, located on the wall of the hall made of 10 kg gold, is thought of as representing east and west.
A mosque and an Ottoman flag were portrayed to represent the East. http://t.co/oflmdxw16p
We have seen significant technological inventions at the Royal Academy of Engineering Sciences.
An advanced version of the MR device in the photo. http://t.co/xcvxk6cdns
We gave a reception in honor of the King and Queen in the mirror room of the hotel we stayed in.
In the reception, our world famous pianists Güher-Süher Pekinel brothers gave a great concert.
Representatives of the Turkish community in Sweden also participated in this reception. I congratulate them once more. the http://t.co/lkohk9chl
I addressed the Swedish Parliament. http://t.co/ur1haxtjuj
On the last day of our visit I visited the city of Uppsala.
I studied Ottoman period books and manuscripts in Uppsala Castle. http://t.co/yn3woklxpb
We had goodbye to Sweden at sunset. http://t.co/juzd4y49og
